Time to (hopefully) start some discussion. Here's a review of Vipers, Nights and French Fries by ThisIsARealAccount (spoilers if you care):

I'm not usually a reader of slice-of-life stuff but it's good so far. The world building is enough to be there but not too much it gets in the way of the story, kind of reminding me of a post-Soviet Russia or post-ww1/2 Germany with political turmoil going on while everyone's just trying to live their lives. For anyone who's worked in fast food, it should bring back memories. There's also a couple details I hope will be Chekov's guns later down the line with illusions to the mob and criminal goings on.

So far, the characters and dialogue are the best part. Both feel real and genuine with Vince coming off as social introvert with enough personality to root for, something that I feel many anons forget when writing human OC's for their stories. Tay is also great to read about as a crass bitch with a hidden softer side, perhaps she feels remorse at what she did during the war. It will be interesting to know what she was doing under the Elders.

In saying that though, the sectoid chick seems like a way better option for Vince than the viper. I know there was that soft side to Tay but come on, the Sectoid is actually interested in him.
